1159
02:09:24,991 --> 02:09:28,912
What a wonderful fish.
What a wonderful fish!

1160
02:09:29,746 --> 02:09:31,789
Yes, wonderful.

1161
02:09:32,248 --> 02:09:36,127
We have to catch it today.
We will catch it today.

1162
02:09:36,585 --> 02:09:41,381
Do the eyes start
on either side of the head?

1163
02:09:41,840 --> 02:09:44,134
Yes, it's a very strange fish.

1164
02:09:44,593 --> 02:09:49,222
When it becomes an adult,
one eye moves across, joins the other.

1165
02:09:50,473 --> 02:09:54,477
Why do they do that?
Maybe it's like a...

1166
02:09:57,813 --> 02:10:02,234
A badge of maturity. They passed
through the nightmare. - Nightmare?

1167
02:10:04,611 --> 02:10:07,989
The nightmare
that separates children from adults.

1168
02:10:09,282 --> 02:10:11,367
Come.
Quickly.

1169
02:10:16,413 --> 02:10:19,500
We got it! We got it!

1170
02:10:20,918 --> 02:10:23,086
We got it! Slowly.

1171
02:10:23,670 --> 02:10:24,671
Slowly!

1172
02:10:25,672 --> 02:10:26,673
Slowly!

1173
02:10:27,507 --> 02:10:30,385
Don't move! Don't move!

1174
02:10:32,261 --> 02:10:37,808
Look, its color changes to match
the ocean floor. - Camouflage.

1175
02:10:38,267 --> 02:10:42,479
If one Arrowtooth Halibut
sinks on top of the head of another,

1176
02:10:42,896 --> 02:10:47,650
